Today marks the 48th anniversary of the Roe v. Wade ruling, which established the right to choose in the United States. In the past four years, reproductive health has faced significant attacks, but the Biden-Harris Administration is committed to protecting this right. They aim to codify Roe v. Wade, appoint judges who respect its precedents, and address health disparities for mothers and infants. Their commitment extends globally, emphasizing the importance of access to healthcare for all individuals. As the new administration begins, the focus is on ensuring everyone has the necessary healthcare support.